  .block.span-11.last
    %h3{:style => "margin-bottom: 12px"} How It Works
    %p
      When you use CallCongress.net to call a legislator, your phone will receive a call from our phone server (effectively, a long distance number). Once you pickup, our server will make a call to the legislator's office. When they pickup, we connect the calls and record the conversation. After the call ends, you can write a brief account of the call and add descriptive tags to help others find your call. This info and the call audio are then automatically posted online for anyone to replay or download.
    %p
      CallCongress.net was inspired by the 
      %a{:href => "http://sunlightfoundation.com/"} Sunlight Foundation's 
      %a{:href => "http://sunlightlabs.com/appsforamerica/"} Apps for America contest. 
      It uses the 
      %a{:href => "http://services.sunlightlabs.com/api/"} Sunlight Labs API 
      to get up-to-date info on Senators and Representatives. 
